repository-code: "https://github.com/rsandrade/archives-worldmap"
url: "https://www.archivesmap.org"
license: AGPL-3.0-or-later
abstract: >-
  The Archives World Map is an open-source web application that enables
  archivists, researchers, and citizens to discover, locate, and contribute
  information about archival institutions on every continent. Created in 2017
  by Ricardo Sodré Andrade during doctoral research at the University of Porto
  and University of Aveiro, it was originally built in PHP and rewritten in
  Python/Flask in 2024–2025. The platform follows FAIR principles with
  ISDIAH-inspired fields, multilingual interface, and open licensing.